# Unified CRM planning scope assumptions:
# - Decision contract: execute.
# - Intent summary: plan an end-to-end internal CRM app for this Next.js repository with landing, authentication, dashboard, customers, and leads surfaces.
# - Requested outcome: deterministic, one-file-per-task planning context that preserves current landing-page behavior while documenting likely CRM expansion surfaces.
# - In scope: document planning assumptions, expected CRM target surfaces, and local persistent-storage ignore patterns for development/runtime artifacts.
# - Out of scope: claiming auth, dashboard, API routes, or database runtime implementation already exists in the repository.
# - Constraints: one repository per conversation, one file per task, maximum 5 tasks per run, preserve unrelated behavior, prefer smallest sufficient scope.
# - Assumptions: App Router remains the routing model; persistent storage may begin with local file or embedded-db artifacts until a future formal backend is introduced.
# - Affected surfaces: app/page.tsx, future auth route, future dashboard route, future customers route, future leads route.
# - Target surface files expected for scoped CRM planning:
#   - app/page.tsx (landing entry)
#   - app/auth/page.tsx (authentication)
#   - app/dashboard/page.tsx (dashboard)
#   - app/dashboard/customers/page.tsx (customers)
#   - app/dashboard/leads/page.tsx (leads)
# - Risk notes: repository currently lacks implemented auth/backend/data modules; avoid treating plan assumptions as shipped features.
# - Success checks: ignore local persistent data artifacts; planning notes stay explicit, concise, and non-speculative.
# - Ignore common local data directories, sqlite files, logs, and lightweight embedded database artifacts to avoid shipping runtime state.
